title: unexpected panic with `cargo check`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code Hi, I am still really new to rust and tried to make a minimal version of this, but kept running into issues. My apologies if this makes the report harder to work with. I'm working on learning rust by contributing to rust-libp2. [Here's my PR](https://github.com/libp2p/rust-libp2p/pull/3224). The very last commit is the one that generated the backtrace below. I'm using VSCode as my IDE and it did not report any errors. Please let me know if there's more steps anyone wants me to do, I've never crashed a compiler before so I'm pretty excited about this and want to help out. :smile: ```Rust // This is the last line I changed before the error occurred, // I basically added in the `#[from]` then ran `cargo check --package=libp2p-floodsub` pub struct CodecError(#[from] prost_codec::Error); ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.65.0 (897e37553 2022-11-02) binary: rustc commit-hash: 897e37553bba8b42751c67658967889d11ecd120 commit-date: 2022-11-02 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.65.0 LLVM version: 15.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.65.0 (897e37553 2022-11-02) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: --crate-type lib -C embed-bitcode=no -C debuginfo=2 -C incremental=[REDACTED] note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden query stack during panic: #0 [evaluate_obligation] evaluating trait selection obligation `protocol::FloodsubProtocol: libp2p_swarm::upgrade::InboundUpgradeSend` #1 [check_well_formed] checking that `layer::Floodsub` is well-formed #2 [analysis] running analysis passes on this crate end of query stack ```
